.com/ucaisersoze.showPublicProfile?language=EN>CaiserSoze</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/5/02 11:00:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10619.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Exact AA skill effects and AC cap?</span><hr size=1> Supposedly, it was posted recently on the Dev board exactly what AA skills affected, and a direct mention to AC soft cap was made - supposedly 1200 is max effective AC, and Combat Stability boosts that to 1320 max effective.... <br><br>Does anyone have a link to where one of the developers said this, or is this just another rumor thats floating around now? I scanned all through the Dev board, could have missed it though... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udrakinn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Drakinn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/5/02 11:06:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10619.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Exact AA skill effects and AC cap?</span><hr size=1> I believe Furor of FoH came up with those numbers<br><br>But i could be wrong.... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uclicksolro.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Click SolRo</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/6/02 12:01:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10619.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Exact AA skill effects and AC cap?</span><hr size=1> I wouldn't mind seeing an explanation on this as well. Common sense says that the &quot;soft cap&quot; shouldn't be affected just because you take less damage in a fight or avoid more due to AA skills. Seems to me, that if anything, the soft cap would be lowered because of these AA skills, not raised. But then again, it's late, im tired and i may be missing something entirely. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ueuripedmoped.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Euriped Moped</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Safehouse Supporter</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/6/02 1:21:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10619.topic&index=3>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Exact AA skill effects and AC cap?</span><hr size=1> Wan't furor.<br><br>It was Afterlife that eventually ran all the tests (Denzalo a monk actually) and got &quot;confirmation&quot; from a &quot;verant employee&quot;<br><br>Dunno if he got the confirmation, but Afterlife is known to know their @#%$ REALLY well, and not lie. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uimmortalis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Immortalis</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/6/02 4:38:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10619.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Exact AA skill effects and AC cap?</span><hr size=1> Combat Stability...atleast for a warrior, raises the softcap from 1200 to 1320.  I have heard that the ac softcap is different for different classes, and warrior is the highest. However I dont know the exact numbers for other classes.<br><br>Ofcourse I have not done any tests on my own (im too lazy), I was just told this about 3 months ago by a good friend and a reliable source.<br><br>Also he said that for every 1 ac you have over 1200 (as a warrior and with combat stability0) you only get 10 percent of the stated ac value.  So for example if you as a warrior had 1300ac with 0 stability points, you would actually only have 1210ac.  That is why after 1200ac it is best to go hp gear over ac.<br><br><br><br>Immortalis the Dark Elven Warlord of Eternal Wrath<br>Ayonae`Ro<br><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=140887">www.magelo.com/eq_view_pr...num=140887</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uaenaitt.showPublicProfile?language=EN>AenaiTT</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/6/02 8:27:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10619.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Exact AA skill effects and AC cap?</span><hr size=1> Is the soft cap the same for melee and caster classes? If so anyone know of what the cap is for casters? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uwalkabout.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Walkabout</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/6/02 8:33:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10619.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Exact AA skill effects and AC cap?</span><hr size=1> Eudiped&gt;It was Afterlife that eventually ran all the tests (Denzalo a monk actually) and got &quot;confirmation&quot; from a &quot;verant employee&quot;<br><br>Denzalo posted on monkly-business he had &quot;proof&quot; there was a softcap. Then 300 posts later he posted his brother had a friend that worked for VI that coughed up a number where the you'd get 10% face value of ac over the alleged 'cap'. No mention of any tests.<br><br>No mention if his brothers friend who gave the 'number' but forgot to give real numbers was a janitor or a developer either. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uwalkabout.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Walkabout</A> at: 4/6/02 8:35:37 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukaelztank.showPublicProfile?language=EN>KAELZTANK</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/7/02 12:16:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10619.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> FLESHGRINDER/HORN OR FLESHGRINDER/FLESHGRINDER</span><hr size=1> I recently picked up a Fleshgrinder and am impressed with damage output.  I am a WARRIOR (sorry for posting on  a rogue site but i figured these readers were very knowledgable so hey, why not)  I currently have grinder main and horn offhand. my question is this:  should I upgrade my secondary to another fleshgrinder for max aggro/damage output?  or keep the 35ac 10 sta that i get from horn?  plz help<br><br>KAELZ<br>60 Ogre Warlord<br>The Nameless <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showNextMessage?topicID=10619.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10619.topic&index=7><img src=http://www.thesafehouse.org/images/reply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.emailToFriend?topicID=10619.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.threadControl?topicID=10619.topic><img src=http://www.thesafehouse.org/images/dagger.jpg border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=10619.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=10619.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub35.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="thesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion">Ma